The paper proposes a method for multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves iterative updates to stabilize the nonstationary environment, which is a common challenge in reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on representing all agents by only one network, which can improve efficiency and avoid memory usage issues, making it relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The method also involves speeding up the interaction with the environment, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
